Text: Is anyone else getting lip sync probs when putting to disc to use in dvd player.As an avi file its going well out.Im also getting this with GI Jones.Everything else works ok just these two.Thanks
I meant as an avi file it works well but when converting the lip sync goes well out.

Are you using ConvertXtoDVD to convert your files to DVD Format?  That usually never has sync issues.
Also check the codecs you are using.  You should have only these 3 installed in this order:
1. FFDShow 2009 version
2. Haali's Matroska Splitter
3. AC3 Filter
Use all default install settings, & ONLY fool with AC3 Filter to get more audio volume.
IMHO
